00:02:14.720 --> 00:02:20.400
input and this string inputs are mapped

00:02:17.520 --> 00:02:22.400
to the PyTorch version of it. So

00:02:20.400 --> 00:02:26.080
basically for example if we have a

00:02:22.400 --> 00:02:29.120
function like get activation it maps the

00:02:26.080 --> 00:02:31.840
choice the string to the to the correct

00:02:29.120 --> 00:02:35.519
syntax. Here I have two additional

00:02:31.840 --> 00:02:37.760
activation that um briefly leaky relu is

00:02:35.519 --> 00:02:40.000
a has a small improvement over the

00:02:37.760 --> 00:02:42.800
standard relu. If you remember wall

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:45.599
outputs uh are zero for any negative

00:02:42.800 --> 00:02:48.239
input. This can lead to uh the dying

00:02:45.599 --> 00:02:51.040
neuron phenomena. But leaky relu allows

00:02:48.239 --> 00:02:53.680
for a tiny nonzero gradient for negative

00:02:51.040 --> 00:02:57.840
inputs. In other word it leaks a little

00:02:53.680 --> 00:03:00.480
and helps the the neuron alive. The next

00:02:57.840 --> 00:03:04.319
one, Jello, is a basically a Gaussian

00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:07.280
error linear unit. Uh it's a smoother uh

00:03:04.319 --> 00:03:09.760
more modern alternative to ALU and it

00:03:07.280 --> 00:03:12.400
has been recently used in uh advanced

00:03:09.760 --> 00:03:15.200
architectures like GPT. Okay, like I

00:03:12.400 --> 00:03:17.280
said, I want to make the design

00:03:15.200 --> 00:03:20.800
flexible. The reason is we want to do

00:03:17.280 --> 00:03:23.280
ablation experiment but also learn

00:03:20.800 --> 00:03:26.239
something along the way. So let's uh

00:03:23.280 --> 00:03:28.480
introduce this deems list uh which is

00:03:26.239 --> 00:03:30.879
basically the components that we are

00:03:28.480 --> 00:03:33.760
going to use in each of this hidden

00:03:30.879 --> 00:03:36.959
layers. So uh if you notice we have

00:03:33.760 --> 00:03:40.720
layers, norms and drops and each one of

00:03:36.959 --> 00:03:43.760
them is a module and n module list and

00:03:40.720 --> 00:03:46.000
uh notice that I didn't use plain python

00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:49.120
list and the reason is this uh n and n

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:52.319
module list is basically uh talks to

00:03:49.120 --> 00:03:54.799
pytor directly. If we use a Python list,

00:03:52.319 --> 00:03:57.040
it will be invisible to PyTorch. Uh you

00:03:54.799 --> 00:03:58.959
can think of it like the the Python list

00:03:57.040 --> 00:04:01.439
like a scratch piece of paper that you

00:03:58.959 --> 00:04:03.840
write the player name. But uh an and

00:04:01.439 --> 00:04:07.200
module list is like an official team

00:04:03.840 --> 00:04:10.239
roster for all of these layers, not

00:04:07.200 --> 00:04:12.480
players. So, PyTorch as a team manager

00:04:10.239 --> 00:04:15.280
uses this roster to correctly find all

00:04:12.480 --> 00:04:19.440
of these parameters for the optimizer

00:04:15.280 --> 00:04:22.479
and also move them to the correct device

00:04:19.440 --> 00:04:24.960
and switch the modes for the layers like

00:04:22.479 --> 00:04:27.360
for example dropout or batch norm during

00:04:24.960 --> 00:04:31.040
