00:10:04.160 --> 00:10:11.120
gives us this paradox about MLP. Why it

00:10:08.560 --> 00:10:13.200
performs well while it really doesn't

00:10:11.120 --> 00:10:16.240
seem to be learning anything. It treats

00:10:13.200 --> 00:10:19.440
the image as a as a shuffled list of

00:10:16.240 --> 00:10:21.920
stock prices. This basically is a hint

00:10:19.440 --> 00:10:24.480
for us that it's really not

00:10:21.920 --> 00:10:27.440
generalizable. If we for example have a

00:10:24.480 --> 00:10:29.519
image of a shirt that is moved in the uh

00:10:27.440 --> 00:10:32.320
it's not centered like what we had in

00:10:29.519 --> 00:10:34.320
the fashion emnest the entire framework

00:10:32.320 --> 00:10:36.880
will collapse in the sense that it

00:10:34.320 --> 00:10:40.160
cannot basically predicts that it's the

00:10:36.880 --> 00:10:43.680
same shirt. So we need something else

00:10:40.160 --> 00:10:46.720
and we can include some of the

00:10:43.680 --> 00:10:49.920
assumptions that we have as inductive

00:10:46.720 --> 00:10:52.480
bias in this new architecture. So for

00:10:49.920 --> 00:10:55.120
example there is an assumption of

00:10:52.480 --> 00:10:57.600
locality. The patterns that we found in

00:10:55.120 --> 00:11:00.000
an image for example the heel of a boot

00:10:57.600 --> 00:11:02.800
can be found in small local regions of

00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:05.440
the image. A very important assumption

00:11:02.800 --> 00:11:08.079
that the patterns is the same whether

00:11:05.440 --> 00:11:12.000
it's in the top left or bottom right of

00:11:08.079 --> 00:11:14.480
the image. We call this an translation

00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:16.880
invariance. MLP doesn't have either of

00:11:14.480 --> 00:11:19.680
them. It basically connects every input

00:11:16.880 --> 00:11:22.079
pixel to every neuron. And this way

00:11:19.680 --> 00:11:24.240
ignores localology. We will discuss a

00:11:22.079 --> 00:11:27.600
new architecture that we are designing

00:11:24.240 --> 00:11:30.560
from ground up with these two biases.

00:11:27.600 --> 00:11:33.120
And this way it allows the architecture

00:11:30.560 --> 00:11:35.680
to learn meaningful spatial features

00:11:33.120 --> 00:11:39.600
that look less like noise like what we

00:11:35.680 --> 00:11:42.720
